      "name": "Hemolysis model literature review",
      "description": "A systematic review of 14 published studies reporting hemolysis index measurements for centrifugal blood pumps was conducted. Reported NIH values were aggregated and compared with model predictions to assess plausibility. The review covered a range of flow rates and rotational speeds broadly consistent with the VAD operating envelope. Reviewers concluded that published data corroborates the model's hemolysis trend predictions and that the aggregated evidence is complementary to and broadly supportive of the model's absolute hemolysis estimates.",
